## Findings

No blocking repo findings remain.

The prior stale OpenAI unit test was wrong after T4: it still expected
OpenAIProvider.complete(..., tools=[...]) to raise a v1.1 pointer error.
inner:4604f0e replaces it with an assertion that the framework tool definition
is translated to OpenAI function-tool shape and sent to the SDK.

The full-suite failures seen under Homebrew Python were environmental:

- Pydantic snapshot drift happened only under Homebrew Python with Pydantic
  2.12.5. The project venv has Pydantic 2.13.4 and passes the snapshot.
- python -m build failed only because ignored generated build/ artifacts
  shadowed the installed build package. Clearing ignored artifacts and using
  the project venv makes the wheel gate pass.

## Autonomy review

The Pentagon autonomy gap remains real. Theo (Test Owner) was active in
Pentagon and produced the red tests. Maya (Code Owner) did not activate from
the handoff, and no live code-owner process was visible during the check. The
implementation and closure were therefore completed by Codex fallback and must
not be counted as Pentagon-only extra-hard autonomy.

